e other users\' genders are `male`/`female`/`other`), so it falls through to `up
.gender IS NULL`, which would filter out almost everyone.\n2. If `preferred_gend
er` is `null`, it defaults to `"both"`, which doesn\'t match anything in the DB,
so the condition evaluates to true only when `up.gender IS NULL`.\n\nThis is a s
erious bug. The default/ fallback value should be `\'all\'`, not `\'both\'`.\n\n
